Class TurnTakerQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.Observable
      • edu.ncsu.csc216.turn_taker.model.turns.TurnTakerQueue
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.Observer

    public class TurnTakerQueue
extends java.util.Observable
implements java.util.Observer
    TurnTakerQueue class can be used to create a TurnTakerQueue that has a SwapLinkedQueue object with a list of TurnTaker.
    Author:
    Sarah Heckman, Stuart Reges, wnwang

      • getTurnTakersAsArray

        public java.lang.String[][] getTurnTakersAsArray​()
        Returns a 2D String array where the first column is the TurnTaker name and the second column is the turnCount. Each row represents a TurnTaker where the first row is the TurnTaker at the front of the queue. If the queue is empty, an empty 2D array is returned.
        Returns:
        2D String array of name and turnCount of the TurnTaker from the queue

      • update

        public void update​(java.util.Observable o,
                   java.lang.Object arg)
        This method is called whenever the observed object is changed. An application calls an Observable object's notifyObservers method to have all the object's observers notified of the change. If the given Observable is a TurnTaker in the SwapLinkedQueue, then the observers of the TurnTakerQueue should be updated. The current instance is passed to notifyObservers().
        Specified by:
        update in interface java.util.Observer
        Parameters:
        o - the observable object.
        arg - an argument passed to the notifyObservers method.
